                        Chargé in Argentina (
                        Cabot
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1179</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1179</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-10-29T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-10-29T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-29T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="1179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1179">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.01/10–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-29T13:00:00-05:00">October 29, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1519. Argentine Chargé<note n="29" xml:id="d1179fn29">Luis S. Luti.</note>
                    informed Braden<note n="30" xml:id="d1179fn30">Spruille Braden, Assistant
                        Secretary of State.</note> he had instructions to ascertain US attitude re
                    recognition of new Venezuelan regime since his Govt desired to follow same
                    course. Braden stated Dept was favorably disposed to accord recognition after
                    consultation with other American republics.</p>
                <pb facs="1430" n="1416" xml:id="pg_1416"/>
                <p>In view of this consultation please inform FonMin immediately of substance of
                    first paragraph of Depts cirtel Oct 27, 8 a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
